AMBASSADOR Edwin Rutageruka, who passed away last Sunday while undergoing medical treatment at the Agha Khan hospital in Dar es Salaam, is expected to be laid to rest today at his Kitobo home village in Missenyi District. Kagera Regional Administrative Secretary (RAS), Prof Faustin Kamuzora said burial arrangements have already been completed. President Samia Suluhu Hassan recently appointed Ambassador Rutageruka the Director of Economic Diplomacy in the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and East African Cooperation. Prior to the appointment, he was the Director General of the Tanzania Trade Development Authority (TANTRADE). TanTrade is a unique public sector organisation, under the Ministry of Industry, Trade and Development, mandated to boost local and global trade. was established by Parliament Act No. 4 of 2009 and commenced its operations on September 3, 2010 (GN No 338). Its establishment followed a repeal of the Act of Parliament No. 15 of 1973 that established the Board of Internal Trade (BIT) and the Act of Parliament No. 5 of 1978 that established the Board of External Trade (BET). It is a statutory organ vested with regulatory, executive, advisory and consultative power of developing and promoting both internal and external trade in Tanzania.